Sure, here are some example sentences that use the word "uzeti" in different forms and positions:

1. *Uzmi* ovu knjigu. (Take this book.)
2. Oni su *uzeli* novac iz banke. (They took money from the bank.)
3. Da li si *uzeo* moj telefon? (Did you take my phone?)
4. Moram *uzeti* pauzu od posla. (I need to take a break from work.)
5. Nije lako *uzeti* životinju iz prirode. (It's not easy to take an animal from nature.)
6. Želiš li *uzeti* kafu sa mnom? (Do you want to take a coffee with me?)
7. *Uzmi* koliko god ti je potrebno. (Take as much as you need.)
8. Proizvod se može *uzeti* samo uz recept. (The product can only be taken with a prescription.)
9. Njihova odluka da *uzmu* odmor bila je dobra. (Their decision to take a vacation was good.)
10. *Uzimajući* u obzir sve okolnosti, odlučili su da odustanu. (Taking all circumstances into account, they decided to give up.)

Note: "uzeti" is the infinitive form of the verb, and the forms used in the sentences above are: "uzmi" (imperative singular), "uzeli" (past tense plural), "uzeo" (past tense singular), "uzeti" (infinitive), "uzeti" (present tense singular), "uzmi" (imperative singular), "uzmi" (imperative singular), "uzeti" (infinitive), "uzmu" (present tense plural), "uzimajući" (present participle).